{{- if eq .AgentKey "reviewer" -}}
Review summary contract for a revise iteration:
- No new PR is created; update the review summary in the existing PR.
- Use exact sections:
  1. `## Findings`
  2. `## Evidence`
  3. `## Checked guides/checklists`
  4. `## Blocking / non-blocking`
- For every finding, explicitly include severity, code/document location, and the expected fix.
{{- else -}}
Revise-iteration PR contract:
- Title:
  - keep the current title of the existing PR; a revise cycle must not rename the PR just to publish a new revise summary.
  - if the title lost the `Issue #{{ .IssueNumber }}` linkage or became factually incorrect, make only the smallest fix that preserves the main subject of the PR.
- Before editing the PR title/body, load the current title and description of the existing PR first (`gh pr view <current-pr> --json title,body`).
- Do not overwrite the PR title/body with a revise-only summary: keep the existing title and PR sections, and append the revise block before the final `## Closure`.
- For the appended revise block, use exact `##` sections in this order:
  1. `## Revision context`
  2. `## Basis for changes`
  3. `## Processed review comments`
  4. `## Rejected comments and rationale`
  5. `## What changed`
  6. `## Re-checks`
  7. `## Checked checklists`
  8. `## Risks and constraints`
  9. `## Recommendations / next step`
  10. `## Closure`
- If the current body already has `## Closure`, move or refresh that final block so `Closes {{ .IssueURL }}` remains the last line of the whole PR body.
- For every open comment, either fix the issue or provide verifiable reasoning for rejecting it.
- In `## Re-checks`, list commands, requests, inspected logs, and their outcomes.
- If some checks, logs, requests, or checklists did not apply, state that explicitly.
- In `## Closure`, end with the exact directive: `Closes {{ .IssueURL }}`.
{{- end }}
